"{\"uid\": \"aljazeera.com-news-2025-4-18-promises-made-in-paris-olympics-run-up-broken-say-undocumented-workers\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Having helped to build a flagship arena, foreign construction workers were promised their papers.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 97, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a flagship arena\", \"from\": 23, \"to\": 39}, {\"ngram\": \"foreign construction workers\", \"from\": 41, \"to\": 69}, {\"ngram\": \"their papers\", \"from\": 84, \"to\": 96}]}, {\"sentence\": \"More than a year later, they remain undocumented.\", \"from\": 98, \"to\": 147, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Save Share Names marked with an asterisk have been changed to protect identities.\", \"from\": 149, \"to\": 232, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Save Share Names\", \"from\": 149, \"to\": 165}, {\"ngram\": \"an asterisk\", \"from\": 178, \"to\": 189}, {\"ngram\": \"identities\", \"from\": 219, \"to\": 229}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris, France -When Moussa*, an undocumented construction worker, joined a wildcat strike at the building site of Paris's Adidas Arena in the early hours of October 17, 2023, he was hoping the protest might lead to him getting the papers he needed to travel home to Mali.\", \"from\": 234, \"to\": 505, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 234, \"end\": 239, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0071832523187585e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 241, \"end\": 247, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999833310487279, \"rank\": 1.2869681674171266e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 348, \"end\": 353, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0071832523187585e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 356, \"end\": 362, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.020614246749095e-25, \"text\": \"Adidas\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\"}, {\"begin\": 500, \"end\": 504, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mali\", \"score\": 0.9999998768817098, \"rank\": 1.2311841627994238e-07, \"text\": \"Mali\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mali\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mali\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"-When Moussa\", \"from\": 248, \"to\": 260}, {\"ngram\": \"an undocumented construction worker\", \"from\": 263, \"to\": 298}, {\"ngram\": \"a wildcat strike\", \"from\": 307, \"to\": 323}, {\"ngram\": \"the building site\", \"from\": 327, \"to\": 344}, {\"ngram\": \"the early hours\", \"from\": 372, \"to\": 387}, {\"ngram\": \"October\", \"from\": 391, \"to\": 398}, {\"ngram\": \"the protest\", \"from\": 423, \"to\": 434}, {\"ngram\": \"the papers\", \"from\": 461, \"to\": 471}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Since arriving in France in 2019, having first boarded a boat from Algeria to Spain, Moussa, 25, has not taken a single vacation.\", \"from\": 507, \"to\": 636, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 525, \"end\": 531, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999833310487279, \"rank\": 1.2869681674171266e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 574, \"end\": 581, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.9999684566692018, \"rank\": 3.152662145013413e-05, \"text\": \"Algeria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}, {\"begin\": 585, \"end\": 590, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Francoist_Spain\", \"score\": 0.8560199226738595, \"rank\": 0.16812933882330386, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Francoist_Spain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Francoist_Spain\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a boat\", \"from\": 562, \"to\": 568}, {\"ngram\": \"Moussa\", \"from\": 592, \"to\": 598}, {\"ngram\": \"a single vacation\", \"from\": 618, \"to\": 635}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After his grandparents died during his time away, he felt an urge to return and mourn with his family.\", \"from\": 637, \"to\": 739, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his grandparents\", \"from\": 643, \"to\": 659}, {\"ngram\": \"his time\", \"from\": 672, \"to\": 680}, {\"ngram\": \"an urge\", \"from\": 695, \"to\": 702}, {\"ngram\": \"his family\", \"from\": 728, \"to\": 738}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For eight months, he worked at the arena, which has 8,000 seats and was being prepared for the 2024 Summer Olympics.\", \"from\": 741, \"to\": 857, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"eight months\", \"from\": 745, \"to\": 757}, {\"ngram\": \"the arena\", \"from\": 772, \"to\": 781}, {\"ngram\": \"8,000 seats\", \"from\": 793, \"to\": 804}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Summer Olympics\", \"from\": 832, \"to\": 856}]}, {\"sentence\": \"More than 400 construction workers operated at the site.\", \"from\": 858, \"to\": 914, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"More than 400 construction workers\", \"from\": 858, \"to\": 892}, {\"ngram\": \"the site\", \"from\": 905, \"to\": 913}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was compensated with normal pay slips by using someone else's papers - a common strategy among undocumented workers.\", \"from\": 916, \"to\": 1035, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"normal pay slips\", \"from\": 940, \"to\": 956}, {\"ngram\": \"someone else's papers\", \"from\": 966, \"to\": 987}, {\"ngram\": \"a common strategy\", \"from\": 990, \"to\": 1007}, {\"ngram\": \"undocumented workers\", \"from\": 1014, \"to\": 1034}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was paid about 75 euros ($85) a day for gruelling 10-hour shifts at the arena - a rate, he said, that did not include transport expenses, masks or other protective gear.\", \"from\": 1036, \"to\": 1208, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"about 75 euros\", \"from\": 1048, \"to\": 1062}, {\"ngram\": \"a day\", \"from\": 1069, \"to\": 1074}, {\"ngram\": \"10-hour shifts\", \"from\": 1089, \"to\": 1103}, {\"ngram\": \"the arena\", \"from\": 1107, \"to\": 1116}, {\"ngram\": \"a rate\", \"from\": 1119, \"to\": 1125}, {\"ngram\": \"transport expenses\", \"from\": 1157, \"to\": 1175}, {\"ngram\": \"masks\", \"from\": 1177, \"to\": 1182}, {\"ngram\": \"other protective gear\", \"from\": 1186, \"to\": 1207}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Moussa's bid paid off.\", \"from\": 1210, \"to\": 1232, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Moussa's bid\", \"from\": 1210, \"to\": 1222}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The workers occupied the site before dawn, blocked it off, and then negotiated all day.\", \"from\": 1234, \"to\": 1321, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The workers\", \"from\": 1234, \"to\": 1245}, {\"ngram\": \"the site\", \"from\": 1255, \"to\": 1263}, {\"ngram\": \"dawn\", \"from\": 1271, \"to\": 1275}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By the evening, they had a deal.\", \"from\": 1322, \"to\": 1354, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the evening\", \"from\": 1325, \"to\": 1336}, {\"ngram\": \"a deal\", \"from\": 1347, \"to\": 1353}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After intense discussions between Moussa's employer, the city of Paris, the workers and their union, a list of 14 undocumented individuals who worked at the site was handed over to the French police prefecture, which deals with visa requests, in order for their paperwork to be processed.\", \"from\": 1356, \"to\": 1644, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1421, \"end\": 1426, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0071832523187585e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1541, \"end\": 1554, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.790620759802774e-45, \"text\": \"French police\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"intense discussions\", \"from\": 1362, \"to\": 1381}, {\"ngram\": \"Moussa's employer\", \"from\": 1390, \"to\": 1407}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 1409, \"to\": 1417}, {\"ngram\": \"the workers\", \"from\": 1428, \"to\": 1439}, {\"ngram\": \"their union\", \"from\": 1444, \"to\": 1455}, {\"ngram\": \"a list\", \"from\": 1457, \"to\": 1463}, {\"ngram\": \"14 undocumented individuals\", \"from\": 1467, \"to\": 1494}, {\"ngram\": \"the site\", \"from\": 1509, \"to\": 1517}, {\"ngram\": \"visa requests\", \"from\": 1584, \"to\": 1597}, {\"ngram\": \"order\", \"from\": 1602, \"to\": 1607}, {\"ngram\": \"their paperwork\", \"from\": 1612, \"to\": 1627}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They signed a framework agreement that would lead to a residency permit and health insurance.\", \"from\": 1646, \"to\": 1739, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a framework agreement\", \"from\": 1658, \"to\": 1679}, {\"ngram\": \"a residency permit\", \"from\": 1699, \"to\": 1717}, {\"ngram\": \"health insurance\", \"from\": 1722, \"to\": 1738}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was signed by the city of Paris, the construction company Bouygues, and several subcontractors.\", \"from\": 1740, \"to\": 1838, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1769, \"end\": 1774, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0071832523187585e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1801, \"end\": 1809, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bouygues\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bouygues\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bouygues\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bouygues\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 1757, \"to\": 1765}, {\"ngram\": \"several subcontractors\", \"from\": 1815, \"to\": 1837}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But 18 months later, the dossiers have still not been approved.\", \"from\": 1840, \"to\": 1903, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the dossiers\", \"from\": 1861, \"to\": 1873}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only one of the 14 has been given an appointment at the Paris prefecture.\", \"from\": 1904, \"to\": 1977, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1960, \"end\": 1965, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0071832523187585e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an appointment\", \"from\": 1938, \"to\": 1952}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A number of the undocumented workers are beginning to wonder whether the delays are by design.\", \"from\": 1979, \"to\": 2073, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A number\", \"from\": 1979, \"to\": 1987}, {\"ngram\": \"the undocumented workers\", \"from\": 1991, \"to\": 2015}, {\"ngram\": \"the delays\", \"from\": 2048, \"to\": 2058}, {\"ngram\": \"design\", \"from\": 2066, \"to\": 2072}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We did not ask for much, just a residency permit and health insurance card.\", \"from\": 2075, \"to\": 2151, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"just a residency permit\", \"from\": 2101, \"to\": 2124}, {\"ngram\": \"health insurance card\", \"from\": 2129, \"to\": 2150}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's our right.\", \"from\": 2152, \"to\": 2167, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our right\", \"from\": 2157, \"to\": 2166}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To this day we do not have the right to work in this country,\\\" Moussa said.\", \"from\": 2168, \"to\": 2243, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this day\", \"from\": 2171, \"to\": 2179}, {\"ngram\": \"the right\", \"from\": 2195, \"to\": 2204}, {\"ngram\": \"this country\", \"from\": 2216, \"to\": 2228}, {\"ngram\": \"Moussa\", \"from\": 2231, \"to\": 2237}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Three of the 14 workers and Rafika Rahmani, a lawyer for the CNT-SO union who focuses on the rights of expatriates, told Al Jazeera that they submitted all the information requested of them more than a year ago.\", \"from\": 2245, \"to\": 2456, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2366, \"end\": 2376, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.5043857198305036e-12, \"text\": \"Al Jazeera\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 14 workers\", \"from\": 2254, \"to\": 2268}, {\"ngram\": \"Rafika Rahmani\", \"from\": 2273, \"to\": 2287}, {\"ngram\": \"a lawyer\", \"from\": 2289, \"to\": 2297}, {\"ngram\": \"the CNT-SO union\", \"from\": 2302, \"to\": 2318}, {\"ngram\": \"the rights\", \"from\": 2334, \"to\": 2344}, {\"ngram\": \"expatriates\", \"from\": 2348, \"to\": 2359}, {\"ngram\": \"all the information\", \"from\": 2397, \"to\": 2416}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We have payslips, we have everything.\", \"from\": 2458, \"to\": 2496, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"payslips\", \"from\": 2467, \"to\": 2475}, {\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 2485, \"to\": 2495}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We are playing by the rules.\", \"from\": 2497, \"to\": 2525, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the rules\", \"from\": 2515, \"to\": 2524}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But so far, we have not had even a single summons,\\\" said Adama*, one of the builders.\", \"from\": 2526, \"to\": 2611, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"even a single summons\", \"from\": 2554, \"to\": 2575}, {\"ngram\": \"Adama\", \"from\": 2583, \"to\": 2588}, {\"ngram\": \"the builders\", \"from\": 2598, \"to\": 2610}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We have no idea why the files are taking so long.\", \"from\": 2612, \"to\": 2662, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no idea\", \"from\": 2621, \"to\": 2628}, {\"ngram\": \"the files\", \"from\": 2633, \"to\": 2642}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We have resubmitted them twice.\", \"from\": 2663, \"to\": 2694, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's like being in prison in France,\\\" added Adama, who has also struggled to find comfortable housing.\", \"from\": 2696, \"to\": 2799, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2726, \"end\": 2732, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999833310487279, \"rank\": 1.2869681674171266e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2741, \"end\": 2746, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Adama\", \"score\": 0.9992366598111041, \"rank\": 0.0007639233220686946, \"text\": \"Adama\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Adama\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Adama\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"prison\", \"from\": 2716, \"to\": 2722}, {\"ngram\": \"comfortable housing\", \"from\": 2779, \"to\": 2798}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He sleeps in a room with 11 other people in the eastern suburb of Montreuil.\", \"from\": 2800, \"to\": 2876, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2866, \"end\": 2875, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Domain_of_Montreuil\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.649243397005288e-16, \"text\": \"Montreuil\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Domain_of_Montreuil\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Domain_of_Montreuil\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a room\", \"from\": 2813, \"to\": 2819}, {\"ngram\": \"11 other people\", \"from\": 2825, \"to\": 2840}, {\"ngram\": \"the eastern suburb\", \"from\": 2844, \"to\": 2862}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's like if you do not have papers in this county, you do not have any value.\\\"\", \"from\": 2877, \"to\": 2957, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"papers\", \"from\": 2907, \"to\": 2913}, {\"ngram\": \"this county\", \"from\": 2917, \"to\": 2928}, {\"ngram\": \"any value\", \"from\": 2946, \"to\": 2955}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite these challenges and his long shifts in construction work, Adama takes evening classes to learn French.\", \"from\": 2959, \"to\": 3070, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3026, \"end\": 3031, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Adama\", \"score\": 0.9992366598111041, \"rank\": 0.0007639233220686946, \"text\": \"Adama\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Adama\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Adama\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these challenges\", \"from\": 2967, \"to\": 2983}, {\"ngram\": \"his long shifts\", \"from\": 2988, \"to\": 3003}, {\"ngram\": \"construction work\", \"from\": 3007, \"to\": 3024}, {\"ngram\": \"evening classes\", \"from\": 3038, \"to\": 3053}, {\"ngram\": \"French\", \"from\": 3063, \"to\": 3069}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In January 2025, CNT-SO, which represents construction and cleaning workers, collectively resubmitted 13 dossiers to the Paris prefecture.\", \"from\": 3072, \"to\": 3210, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3193, \"end\": 3198, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0071832523187585e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"January\", \"from\": 3075, \"to\": 3082}, {\"ngram\": \"CNT-SO\", \"from\": 3089, \"to\": 3095}, {\"ngram\": \"construction and cleaning workers\", \"from\": 3114, \"to\": 3147}, {\"ngram\": \"13 dossiers\", \"from\": 3174, \"to\": 3185}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The files are still blocked, despite the fact that I have re-applied for these 13 people,\\\" Rahmani told Al Jazeera.\", \"from\": 3212, \"to\": 3328, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3317, \"end\": 3327, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.5043857198305036e-12, \"text\": \"Al Jazeera\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The files\", \"from\": 3213, \"to\": 3222}, {\"ngram\": \"the fact\", \"from\": 3250, \"to\": 3258}, {\"ngram\": \"these 13 people\", \"from\": 3286, \"to\": 3301}, {\"ngram\": \"Rahmani\", \"from\": 3304, \"to\": 3311}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She suspects that the lack of response is a form of backlash, as the strikes unveiled poor working conditions in France in the lead-up to the Olympics.\", \"from\": 3330, \"to\": 3481, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3443, \"end\": 3449, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999833310487279, \"rank\": 1.2869681674171266e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the lack\", \"from\": 3348, \"to\": 3356}, {\"ngram\": \"response\", \"from\": 3360, \"to\": 3368}, {\"ngram\": \"a form\", \"from\": 3372, \"to\": 3378}, {\"ngram\": \"backlash\", \"from\": 3382, \"to\": 3390}, {\"ngram\": \"the strikes\", \"from\": 3395, \"to\": 3406}, {\"ngram\": \"poor working conditions\", \"from\": 3416, \"to\": 3439}, {\"ngram\": \"the lead-up\", \"from\": 3453, \"to\": 3464}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 3468, \"to\": 3480}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's revenge,\\\" Rahmani said.\", \"from\": 3483, \"to\": 3512, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"revenge\", \"from\": 3489, \"to\": 3496}, {\"ngram\": \"Rahmani\", \"from\": 3499, \"to\": 3506}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"For them, the [striking workers] gave [France] a bad image, even if it's the reality.\\\"\", \"from\": 3513, \"to\": 3600, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3553, \"end\": 3559, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999833310487279, \"rank\": 1.2869681674171266e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the [striking workers\", \"from\": 3524, \"to\": 3545}, {\"ngram\": \"a bad image\", \"from\": 3561, \"to\": 3572}, {\"ngram\": \"the reality\", \"from\": 3587, \"to\": 3598}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The project developer and two subcontracting companies - which have not responded to Al Jazeera's request for comment - have allegedly prevented some workers from returning to construction sites, meaning they have lost jobs and housing.\", \"from\": 3602, \"to\": 3838, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3687, \"end\": 3697, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.5043857198305036e-12, \"text\": \"Al Jazeera\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The project developer\", \"from\": 3602, \"to\": 3623}, {\"ngram\": \"two subcontracting companies\", \"from\": 3628, \"to\": 3656}, {\"ngram\": \"comment\", \"from\": 3712, \"to\": 3719}, {\"ngram\": \"some workers\", \"from\": 3747, \"to\": 3759}, {\"ngram\": \"construction sites\", \"from\": 3778, \"to\": 3796}, {\"ngram\": \"jobs\", \"from\": 3821, \"to\": 3825}, {\"ngram\": \"housing\", \"from\": 3830, \"to\": 3837}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to Adama, at least three colleagues have not worked since October 2023, and rely on charities to subsidise their food and housing.\", \"from\": 3840, \"to\": 3980, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3853, \"end\": 3858, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Adama\", \"score\": 0.9992366598111041, \"rank\": 0.0007639233220686946, \"text\": \"Adama\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Adama\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Adama\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"at least three colleagues\", \"from\": 3860, \"to\": 3885}, {\"ngram\": \"October\", \"from\": 3908, \"to\": 3915}, {\"ngram\": \"charities\", \"from\": 3934, \"to\": 3943}, {\"ngram\": \"their food\", \"from\": 3957, \"to\": 3967}, {\"ngram\": \"housing\", \"from\": 3972, \"to\": 3979}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We have information that the company employing them did not reinstate them.\", \"from\": 3982, \"to\": 4058, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"information\", \"from\": 3991, \"to\": 4002}, {\"ngram\": \"the company\", \"from\": 4008, \"to\": 4019}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a disciplinary measure against the strike in which they had participated,\\\" Jean-Francois Coulomme, a representative of left-wing La France Insoumise party, told Al Jazeera.\", \"from\": 4059, \"to\": 4238, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4195, \"end\": 4214, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_France_Insoumise\", \"score\": 0.9999999999754436, \"rank\": 2.4732441154854765e-11, \"text\": \"La France Insoumise\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_France_Insoumise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_France_Insoumise\"}, {\"begin\": 4227, \"end\": 4237, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.5043857198305036e-12, \"text\": \"Al Jazeera\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a disciplinary measure\", \"from\": 4066, \"to\": 4088}, {\"ngram\": \"the strike\", \"from\": 4097, \"to\": 4107}, {\"ngram\": \",\\\" Jean-Francois Coulomme\", \"from\": 4138, \"to\": 4163}, {\"ngram\": \"a representative\", \"from\": 4165, \"to\": 4181}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's a strategy of ostracising these employees in particular.\\\"\", \"from\": 4239, \"to\": 4302, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a strategy\", \"from\": 4245, \"to\": 4255}, {\"ngram\": \"these employees\", \"from\": 4271, \"to\": 4286}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In February, Coulomme wrote to France's interior minister via a government accountability mechanism on the \\\"fate of the files submitted to the Paris Prefecture\\\", demanding \\\"the legitimate regularisation of these workers\\\".\", \"from\": 4304, \"to\": 4525, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4335, \"end\": 4341, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999833310487279, \"rank\": 1.2869681674171266e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"February\", \"from\": 4307, \"to\": 4315}, {\"ngram\": \"Coulomme\", \"from\": 4317, \"to\": 4325}, {\"ngram\": \"a government accountability mechanism\", \"from\": 4366, \"to\": 4403}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"fate\", \"from\": 4407, \"to\": 4416}, {\"ngram\": \"the files\", \"from\": 4420, \"to\": 4429}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Prefecture\", \"from\": 4443, \"to\": 4463}, {\"ngram\": \"the legitimate regularisation\", \"from\": 4477, \"to\": 4506}, {\"ngram\": \"these workers\", \"from\": 4510, \"to\": 4523}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The letter remains unanswered.\", \"from\": 4527, \"to\": 4557, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The letter\", \"from\": 4527, \"to\": 4537}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The arena workers' case is representative of a systemic problem.\", \"from\": 4559, \"to\": 4624, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The arena workers' case\", \"from\": 4560, \"to\": 4583}, {\"ngram\": \"a systemic problem\", \"from\": 4605, \"to\": 4623}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a good illustration of the fact that these workers are silenced due to the [precariousness] of their administrative situation,\\\" Colomme said.\", \"from\": 4625, \"to\": 4771, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a good illustration\", \"from\": 4630, \"to\": 4649}, {\"ngram\": \"the fact\", \"from\": 4653, \"to\": 4661}, {\"ngram\": \"these workers\", \"from\": 4667, \"to\": 4680}, {\"ngram\": \"the [precariousness\", \"from\": 4701, \"to\": 4720}, {\"ngram\": \"their administrative situation\", \"from\": 4725, \"to\": 4755}, {\"ngram\": \"Colomme\", \"from\": 4758, \"to\": 4765}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The CNT-SO union and so-called Gilets Noirs, or Black Vests - a collective of mostly undocumented migrants working to get administrative regularisation and housing rights for migrants in France - tried expediting the process through the city of Paris, as the city was one of the negotiating parties.\", \"from\": 4773, \"to\": 5072, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4804, \"end\": 4816, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gilets_noirs\", \"score\": 0.9999999401648001, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gilets Noirs\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gilets_noirs\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gilets_noirs\"}, {\"begin\": 4821, \"end\": 4826, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Black_people\", \"score\": 0.9812206586982355, \"rank\": 0.01913875444192121, \"text\": \"Black\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Black_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Black_people\"}, {\"begin\": 4960, \"end\": 4966, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999833310487279, \"rank\": 1.2869681674171266e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 5018, \"end\": 5023, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0071832523187585e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The CNT-SO union\", \"from\": 4773, \"to\": 4789}, {\"ngram\": \"a collective\", \"from\": 4835, \"to\": 4847}, {\"ngram\": \"mostly undocumented migrants\", \"from\": 4851, \"to\": 4879}, {\"ngram\": \"administrative regularisation\", \"from\": 4895, \"to\": 4924}, {\"ngram\": \"housing rights\", \"from\": 4929, \"to\": 4943}, {\"ngram\": \"migrants\", \"from\": 4948, \"to\": 4956}, {\"ngram\": \"the process\", \"from\": 4986, \"to\": 4997}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 5006, \"to\": 5014}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 5028, \"to\": 5036}, {\"ngram\": \"the negotiating parties\", \"from\": 5048, \"to\": 5071}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We have plugged a few more holes by going through the mayor of Paris, because they are the intermediary between our contacts and the Paris prefecture.\", \"from\": 5074, \"to\": 5225, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5138, \"end\": 5143, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0071832523187585e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 5208, \"end\": 5213, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0071832523187585e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a few more holes\", \"from\": 5091, \"to\": 5107}, {\"ngram\": \"the mayor\", \"from\": 5125, \"to\": 5134}, {\"ngram\": \"the intermediary\", \"from\": 5162, \"to\": 5178}, {\"ngram\": \"our contacts\", \"from\": 5187, \"to\": 5199}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We want to know what the situation is,\\\" Doums, a spokesperson for the Gilets Noirs, told Al Jazeera.\", \"from\": 5226, \"to\": 5326, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5315, \"end\": 5325, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.5043857198305036e-12, \"text\": \"Al Jazeera\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the situation\", \"from\": 5247, \"to\": 5260}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\" Doums\", \"from\": 5264, \"to\": 5271}, {\"ngram\": \"a spokesperson\", \"from\": 5273, \"to\": 5287}, {\"ngram\": \"the Gilets Noirs\", \"from\": 5292, \"to\": 5308}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Today, the situation is still, let us not say totally blocked, but a bit blocked at the level of the prefecture.\\\"\", \"from\": 5327, \"to\": 5441, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the situation\", \"from\": 5335, \"to\": 5348}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 5363, \"to\": 5365}, {\"ngram\": \"the level\", \"from\": 5412, \"to\": 5421}, {\"ngram\": \"the prefecture\", \"from\": 5425, \"to\": 5439}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Colomme suggested the Ministry of the Interior is preventing the dossiers from being approved.\", \"from\": 5443, \"to\": 5537, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Colomme\", \"from\": 5443, \"to\": 5450}, {\"ngram\": \"the Ministry\", \"from\": 5461, \"to\": 5473}, {\"ngram\": \"the Interior\", \"from\": 5477, \"to\": 5489}, {\"ngram\": \"the dossiers\", \"from\": 5504, \"to\": 5516}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The prefectures take their orders from the ministry.\", \"from\": 5539, \"to\": 5592, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The prefectures\", \"from\": 5540, \"to\": 5555}, {\"ngram\": \"their orders\", \"from\": 5561, \"to\": 5573}, {\"ngram\": \"the ministry\", \"from\": 5579, \"to\": 5591}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So as far as we are concerned, the prefects simply apply the directives of the minister in charge,\\\" Coulomme said.\", \"from\": 5593, \"to\": 5707, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the prefects\", \"from\": 5624, \"to\": 5636}, {\"ngram\": \"the directives\", \"from\": 5650, \"to\": 5664}, {\"ngram\": \"the minister\", \"from\": 5668, \"to\": 5680}, {\"ngram\": \"charge\", \"from\": 5684, \"to\": 5690}, {\"ngram\": \"Coulomme\", \"from\": 5693, \"to\": 5701}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Al Jazeera contacted the minister of the interior and Paris prefecture, but did not receive a comment by the time of publication.\", \"from\": 5709, \"to\": 5838, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5709, \"end\": 5719, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.5043857198305036e-12, \"text\": \"Al Jazeera\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\"}, {\"begin\": 5763, \"end\": 5768, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0071832523187585e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the minister\", \"from\": 5730, \"to\": 5742}, {\"ngram\": \"a comment\", \"from\": 5801, \"to\": 5810}, {\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 5814, \"to\": 5822}, {\"ngram\": \"publication\", \"from\": 5826, \"to\": 5837}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The initially swift response and negotiations are a typical reaction when a city is scrutinised before major international events, but often there is no follow-through when the hype dies down.\", \"from\": 5840, \"to\": 6032, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The initially swift response\", \"from\": 5840, \"to\": 5868}, {\"ngram\": \"negotiations\", \"from\": 5873, \"to\": 5885}, {\"ngram\": \"a typical reaction\", \"from\": 5890, \"to\": 5908}, {\"ngram\": \"a city\", \"from\": 5914, \"to\": 5920}, {\"ngram\": \"major international events\", \"from\": 5943, \"to\": 5969}, {\"ngram\": \"no follow-through\", \"from\": 5990, \"to\": 6007}, {\"ngram\": \"the hype\", \"from\": 6013, \"to\": 6021}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The state of exception that the Olympics bring can be really important for leveraging gains for workers,\\\" Jules Boykoff, researcher and author of the book Power Games: A Political History of the Olympics, told Al Jazeera.\", \"from\": 6034, \"to\": 6256, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6141, \"end\": 6154, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jules_Boykoff\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jules Boykoff\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jules_Boykoff\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jules_Boykoff\"}, {\"begin\": 6245, \"end\": 6255, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.5043857198305036e-12, \"text\": \"Al Jazeera\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The state\", \"from\": 6035, \"to\": 6044}, {\"ngram\": \"exception\", \"from\": 6048, \"to\": 6057}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 6063, \"to\": 6075}, {\"ngram\": \"gains\", \"from\": 6121, \"to\": 6126}, {\"ngram\": \"workers\", \"from\": 6131, \"to\": 6138}, {\"ngram\": \"researcher\", \"from\": 6156, \"to\": 6166}, {\"ngram\": \"author\", \"from\": 6171, \"to\": 6177}, {\"ngram\": \"the book\", \"from\": 6181, \"to\": 6189}, {\"ngram\": \"Power Games\", \"from\": 6190, \"to\": 6201}, {\"ngram\": \"A Political History\", \"from\": 6203, \"to\": 6222}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 6226, \"to\": 6238}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The key is to lock in those gains while the hot glare of the Olympic spotlight still shines in your city.\", \"from\": 6257, \"to\": 6363, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The key\", \"from\": 6258, \"to\": 6265}, {\"ngram\": \"those gains\", \"from\": 6280, \"to\": 6291}, {\"ngram\": \"the hot glare\", \"from\": 6298, \"to\": 6311}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic spotlight\", \"from\": 6315, \"to\": 6336}, {\"ngram\": \"your city\", \"from\": 6353, \"to\": 6362}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After that, it becomes much more difficult to take advantage of that Olympic moment to make promises to these workers.\\\"\", \"from\": 6364, \"to\": 6483, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"advantage\", \"from\": 6415, \"to\": 6424}, {\"ngram\": \"that Olympic moment\", \"from\": 6428, \"to\": 6447}, {\"ngram\": \"promises\", \"from\": 6456, \"to\": 6464}, {\"ngram\": \"these workers\", \"from\": 6468, \"to\": 6481}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This can be an opportune time for people to push for rights, but the Olympics and other major sporting events also open the door for exploitation, especially for people in precarious situations like undocumented workers.\", \"from\": 6485, \"to\": 6705, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an opportune time\", \"from\": 6497, \"to\": 6514}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 6519, \"to\": 6525}, {\"ngram\": \"rights\", \"from\": 6538, \"to\": 6544}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 6550, \"to\": 6562}, {\"ngram\": \"other major sporting events\", \"from\": 6567, \"to\": 6594}, {\"ngram\": \"the door\", \"from\": 6605, \"to\": 6613}, {\"ngram\": \"exploitation\", \"from\": 6618, \"to\": 6630}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 6647, \"to\": 6653}, {\"ngram\": \"precarious situations\", \"from\": 6657, \"to\": 6678}, {\"ngram\": \"undocumented workers\", \"from\": 6684, \"to\": 6704}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This is just one more egregious example of taking advantage of people to create a sporting event that claims to benefit the many but actually just benefits the few,\\\" Boykoff said.\", \"from\": 6707, \"to\": 6887, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"just one more egregious example\", \"from\": 6716, \"to\": 6747}, {\"ngram\": \"advantage\", \"from\": 6758, \"to\": 6767}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 6771, \"to\": 6777}, {\"ngram\": \"a sporting event\", \"from\": 6788, \"to\": 6804}, {\"ngram\": \"Boykoff\", \"from\": 6874, \"to\": 6881}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Olympics tend to spotlight what we might call surplus populations - whether we are talking about expendable athletes or expendable workers who make the Olympic spectacle possible.\\\"\", \"from\": 6888, \"to\": 7073, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Olympics\", \"from\": 6889, \"to\": 6901}, {\"ngram\": \"surplus populations\", \"from\": 6939, \"to\": 6958}, {\"ngram\": \"expendable athletes\", \"from\": 6990, \"to\": 7009}, {\"ngram\": \"expendable workers\", \"from\": 7013, \"to\": 7031}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic spectacle\", \"from\": 7041, \"to\": 7062}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rahmani said, \\\"During the strike, all these people came and made big promises \\u2026 These deputies and senators come to a demonstration or strike and make a commitment to regularise these workers, but in the end, there is no follow-up, and they tell you that they have no power.\\\"\", \"from\": 7075, \"to\": 7350, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Rahmani\", \"from\": 7075, \"to\": 7082}, {\"ngram\": \"the strike\", \"from\": 7097, \"to\": 7107}, {\"ngram\": \"all these people\", \"from\": 7109, \"to\": 7125}, {\"ngram\": \"big promises\", \"from\": 7140, \"to\": 7152}, {\"ngram\": \"These deputies\", \"from\": 7155, \"to\": 7169}, {\"ngram\": \"senators\", \"from\": 7174, \"to\": 7182}, {\"ngram\": \"a demonstration\", \"from\": 7191, \"to\": 7206}, {\"ngram\": \"a commitment\", \"from\": 7226, \"to\": 7238}, {\"ngram\": \"these workers\", \"from\": 7253, \"to\": 7266}, {\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 7275, \"to\": 7282}, {\"ngram\": \"no follow-up\", \"from\": 7293, \"to\": 7305}, {\"ngram\": \"no power\", \"from\": 7340, \"to\": 7348}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For years, France's government has hardened its stance against immigration.\", \"from\": 7352, \"to\": 7427, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7363, \"end\": 7369, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999833310487279, \"rank\": 1.2869681674171266e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"years\", \"from\": 7356, \"to\": 7361}, {\"ngram\": \"its stance\", \"from\": 7396, \"to\": 7406}, {\"ngram\": \"immigration\", \"from\": 7415, \"to\": 7426}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In December 2023, the French Parliament passed a controversial immigration law that differentiates between foreigners \\\"in a situation of employment\\\" and those who are not.\", \"from\": 7429, \"to\": 7600, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7451, \"end\": 7468, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Parliament\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5163047586682686e-46, \"text\": \"French Parliament\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q11204\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Parliament\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Parliament\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"December\", \"from\": 7432, \"to\": 7440}, {\"ngram\": \"a controversial immigration law\", \"from\": 7476, \"to\": 7507}, {\"ngram\": \"foreigners\", \"from\": 7536, \"to\": 7546}, {\"ngram\": \"a situation\", \"from\": 7551, \"to\": 7562}, {\"ngram\": \"employment\", \"from\": 7566, \"to\": 7576}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The measure made it more difficult to receive social benefits for out-of-work expatriates.\", \"from\": 7601, \"to\": 7691, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The measure\", \"from\": 7601, \"to\": 7612}, {\"ngram\": \"social benefits\", \"from\": 7647, \"to\": 7662}, {\"ngram\": \"work\", \"from\": 7674, \"to\": 7678}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The new regulations have played out in workplaces.\", \"from\": 7693, \"to\": 7743, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The new regulations\", \"from\": 7693, \"to\": 7712}, {\"ngram\": \"workplaces\", \"from\": 7732, \"to\": 7742}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Between 2023 and 2024, according to official figures, the number of undocumented workers who were regularised dipped by 10 percent.\", \"from\": 7745, \"to\": 7876, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"official figures\", \"from\": 7781, \"to\": 7797}, {\"ngram\": \"the number\", \"from\": 7799, \"to\": 7809}, {\"ngram\": \"undocumented workers\", \"from\": 7813, \"to\": 7833}, {\"ngram\": \"10 percent\", \"from\": 7865, \"to\": 7875}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Deportations, on the other hand, rose by more than a quarter.\", \"from\": 7877, \"to\": 7938, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Deportations\", \"from\": 7877, \"to\": 7889}, {\"ngram\": \"the other hand\", \"from\": 7894, \"to\": 7908}, {\"ngram\": \"more than a quarter\", \"from\": 7918, \"to\": 7937}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This ideology is currently affecting our country as a whole, with an instrumentalisation of the migration issue, which means we are taking a totally utilitarian approach,\\\" Coul